---
// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { release } from "../../data/release";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Install"
  description="Install Peeknook from the release DMG, set up Ollama and Gemma 4, and grant Screen Recording."
  current="install"
>
  <h1 class="page-title">Install Peeknook</h1>
  <p class="page-intro">
    Production installs use the signed app from GitHub Releases, not
    <code>swift run</code>. macOS ties Screen Recording to the app bundle ID.
  </p>

  <ol class="steps">
    <li>
      <h2>1. Download the DMG</h2>
      <p>
        Get <a href={release.dmgURL}>Peeknook-{release.version}.dmg</a> from this
        site or
        <a href={release.latestReleasesURL}>GitHub Releases</a>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>2. Move Peeknook to Applications</h2>
      <p>
        Open the DMG and drag <strong>Peeknook</strong> into
        <strong>Applications</strong>. Eject the disk image when you are done.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>3. First launch</h2>
      <p>
        Open Peeknook from Applications. If macOS shows a Gatekeeper prompt,
        choose Open. The app identity is <code>com.peeknook.app</code>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>4. Get ready (in-app setup)</h2>
      <p>Peeknook walks you through three prerequisites:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Ollama</strong>: install the
          <a href="https://formulae.brew.sh/cask/ollama-app">ollama-app</a> cask,
          not the Homebrew formula. The cask includes the runner Peeknook needs.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Gemma 4</strong>: pull a tag that fits your RAM, for example
          <code>gemma4:e2b</code>, <code>gemma4:e4b</code>, or
          <code>gemma4:26b</code>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Screen Recording</strong>: grant permission to
          <strong>Peeknook</strong> in System Settings. This is required for
          vision capture.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>5. Capture and answer</h2>
      <p>
        Toggle the nook with ⌘⌥; and capture with ⌘⇧P. Optional Accessibility
        permission adds selected text from the focused field.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Developing from source?</strong> <code>swift run Peeknook</code> is
    for contributors only. macOS may list a separate Screen Recording entry
    (Terminal, Swift, or the debug binary). Granting permission there does not
    grant it to the shipped <strong>Peeknook</strong> app in Applications.
  </div>

  <div class="cta-row" style="margin-top: 2rem">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href={release.dmgURL}>Download for Mac</a>
    <a class="btn btn-ghost" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`}>Back to home</a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
